TITLE: Basic Loader Implementation with useLoader Hook in TSX
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the basic implementation of a loader function and accessing its data on the client using the useLoader hook. The loader runs on the server and returns data that can be safely passed to the client.
SOURCE: https://github.com/onejs/one/blob/main/apps/onestack.dev/data/docs/routing-loader.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useLoader } from 'one'

export async function loader() {
  return {
    user: 'tamagui'
  }
}

export default function HomePage() {
  const data = useLoader(loader)

  return (
    <p>
      {data.user}
    </p>
  )
}
```

