TITLE: Using useFocusEffect with React Navigation in a Profile Component
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use useFocusEffect to subscribe to API updates only when a profile screen is focused. The hook accepts a callback function and a dependencies array, similar to useEffect, but executes only when the route gains focus in navigation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/onejs/one/blob/main/apps/onestack.dev/data/docs/hooks-useFocusEffect.mdx#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useFocusEffect } from '@react-navigation/native'
import { useCallback } from 'react'

function Profile({ userId }) {
  const [user, setUser] = React.useState(null)

  useFocusEffect(
    () => {
      const unsubscribe = API.subscribe(userId, (user) => setUser(user))
      return () => unsubscribe()
    },
    [userId]
  )

  return <ProfileContent user={user} />
}
```

